Mixed ploidy simulation

Trevor Faske

This Rmarkdown is a generates fake mixed ploidy data and estimates different ways of summarizing

Loading packages

Generate data

sample from beta()

generate geno

set.seed(666)
nloci <- 1000
nind  <- 300
n2 <- nind*0.50
n4 <- nind-n2

pl_list <- c(rep(2,times=n2),
             rep(4,times=n4))

locus.p.sim <- rbeta(nloci, 0.4, 0.6)
hist(locus.p.sim)

#test2 <- rbinom(nind, size=2, prob=.5) + rnorm(nind,0,0.05)
#test4 <- rbinom(nind, size=4, prob=.5) + rnorm(nind,0,0.05)
#hist(test2)
#hist(test4)

#test2_unc <- rnorm(nind,0,0.05)
#hist(test2_unc)

geno2 <- matrix(0, nrow=n2, ncol=nloci)
geno4 <- matrix(0, nrow=n4, ncol=nloci)
for(i in 1:nloci){
  
  count <- 1
  while(count == 1){
    geno2[,i] <- rbinom(n2, size=2, prob=locus.p.sim[i]) #+ rnorm(n2,0,0.05)
    geno4[,i] <- rbinom(n4, size=4, prob=locus.p.sim[i]) #+ rnorm(n4,0,0.05)
  
    #make sure variation
    g <- c(geno2[,i]*2,geno4[,i])
    count <- length(table(g))
  }
  
  #sloppy way to fix above and below bounds if variation added
  #geno2[which(geno2 < 0)] <- 0 
  #geno4[which(geno4 < 0)] <- 0 
  
  #geno2[which(geno2 > 2)] <- 2 
  #geno4[which(geno4 > 4)] <- 4 
}

geno <- rbind(geno2,geno4)

geno <- cbind(pl_list,geno)

write.csv(geno,'geno.csv',row.names = F)

summarize in various ways

Take homes: dividing by ploidy or multiplying diploid by 2 scales well BUT diploids have higher sd on average. Allele frequencies same though. Maybe patterson method right way to go.

geno <- read.csv('geno.csv')

geno_af <- apply(geno,2,function(d) sum(d,na.rm=TRUE)/(2*length(d)))

## pca with patterson standardization

#### mult pat ####

colmean<-apply(geno_mult,2,mean,na.rm=TRUE)
  
normalize<-matrix(nrow = nrow(geno_mult),ncol=ncol(geno_mult))
#af<-colmean/4 #4 cause ploidy
af4 <- apply(geno_mult,2,function(d) sum(d,na.rm=TRUE)/(4*length(d)))
#plot(af,af4)
  
for (m in 1:length(af4)){
  nr<-geno_mult[ ,m]-colmean[m]
  #dn<-sqrt(2*abs(af[m]*(1-af[m])))
  dn<-sqrt(2*abs(af4[m]*(1-af4[m])))
  normalize[ ,m]<-nr/dn
}

#norm_sd <- apply(normalize,2,sd)
#which(is.na(norm_sd)) 

pat_mult_pca <- prcomp(as.matrix(normalize),scale. = F, center = F)
pve <- summary(pat_mult_pca)$importance[2,1:5]
summary(pat_mult_pca)$importance[2:3,1:5]
##                            PC1     PC2     PC3     PC4     PC5
## Proportion of Variance 0.00888 0.00873 0.00855 0.00850 0.00840
## Cumulative Proportion  0.00888 0.01761 0.02616 0.03467 0.04307
pat_mult_pca_df <- cbind(data.frame(pl=pl_list),pat_mult_pca$x[,1:5])

pca_pat_mult <- ggplot(data = pat_mult_pca_df,
                         aes(x=PC1,y=PC2,fill=as.character(pl))) + 
  geom_point(pch=21,colour='black',size = 5) + 
  xlab(paste("PC",1," (",pve[1]*100,"%)",sep="")) + ylab(paste("PC",2," (",pve[2]*100,"%)",sep=""))  +
  scale_fill_npg(name='Ploidy:') + 
  #scale_fill_gradientn(name='Longitude:',colours = pal) +
  theme_bw() + 
  theme(#legend.position = 'none',
    axis.text = element_text(size=11), 
    axis.title = element_text(size = 13, colour="black",face = "bold",vjust = 1),
    panel.border = element_rect(size = 1.5, colour = "black"),
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),

#### mult pat ####

colmean<-apply(geno_mult,2,mean,na.rm=TRUE)
geno_mult2_sd <- apply(geno_mult[1:n2,],2,sd)
geno_mult4_sd <- apply(geno_mult[(n2+1):nind,],2,sd)

g2_z <- matrix(nrow = n2,ncol=nloci)
g4_z <- matrix(nrow = n4,ncol=nloci)
for (i in 1:nloci){
  if(geno_mult2_sd[i] == 0){
    g2_z[,i] <- (geno_mult[1:n2,i] - colmean[i])
  }else{
    g2_z[,i] <- (geno_mult[1:n2,i] - colmean[i])/geno_mult2_sd[i]
  }
  if(geno_mult4_sd[i] == 0){
    g4_z[,i] <- (geno_mult[(n2+1):nind,i] - colmean[i])
  }else{
    g4_z[,i] <- (geno_mult[(n2+1):nind,i] - colmean[i])/geno_mult4_sd[i]

g2 <- geno[1:n2,]
g4 <- geno[(n2+1):nind,]
mean2<-apply(g2,2,mean,na.rm=TRUE)
mean4<-apply(g4,2,mean,na.rm=TRUE)
sd2<-apply(g2,2,sd,na.rm=TRUE)
sd4<-apply(g4,2,sd,na.rm=TRUE)

g2_z <- matrix(nrow = n2,ncol=nloci)
g4_z <- matrix(nrow = n4,ncol=nloci)
for (i in 1:nloci){
  if(sd2[i] == 0){
    g2_z[,i] <- (g2[,i] - mean2[i])
  }else{
    g2_z[,i] <- (g2[,i] - mean2[i])/sd2[i]

    g4_z[,i] <- (g4[,i] - mean4[i])/sd4[i]
  }
}
